(1)Enhance the capacity of Parliamentary committees to scrutinize draft laws, oversee the executive branch of government and represent citizens;
(2)Secretariat staff of the Senate and National Assembly have the resources and capacity to support the work of Parliamentarians;
(3) Civil society provided the knowledge and skills to effectively articulate the concerns of citizens to Parliamentarians; and,
(4) Aid and support to the Federal Parliament is better coordinated.
